Super Eagles and Granada CF defensive midfielder, Ramon Azeez, believes he can  play anywhere after starring in the very competitive .Spanish LaLiga. Azeez, 27, has played all his football in Spain, featuring for Almeria, CD Lugo, and Granada CF since he arrived in the football-crazy country in 2011. The former National U20 captain explained that football style, tactics, and techniques are unique in Spain which when well understood, can aid a player to adapt to top-notch football anywhere in the world. “Football in Spain is top notch and of high quality. If one can successfully play in the LaLiga, I think it will be safe to say you can anywhere else in the world, “ Azeez told AOIFootball.com